          <p>I haven't run across any restrictions, but maybe someone else will have other experiences.  Typically the 401(k), 403(b), etc. would be administered by an outside financial institution, although it does make me wonder if additional concerns could arise if the plan was administered internally.  Are there any particular areas of concern you think might be an issue here?</p>


